2026-05-16 19:09:22 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #1 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] submit_repaired_code({"code": "from pathlib import Path\nimport pandas as pd\n\nbase = Path('other-benchmarks/Kramabench/data/environment/input')\nfiles = {\n    'constitution': base / 'constitution_beach_datasheet.csv',\n    'pleasure_castle': base / 'pleasure_bay_and_castle_island_beach_datasheet.csv',\n}\n\n\ndef load_tidy(path: Path) -> pd.DataFrame:\n    # Skip the title row; next two rows form a multi-row header\n    df = pd.read_csv(path, skiprows=1, header=[0, 1])\n\n    cols = df.columns.to_frame(index=False)\n    # Forward-fill top-level location names across paired Tag/Enterococcus columns\n    cols.iloc[:, 0] = cols.iloc[:, 0].replace(r'^Unnamed.*', pd.NA, regex=True).ffill()\n\n    flat_cols = []\n    for top, bottom in cols.itertuples(index=False, name=None):\n        parts = [str(x).strip() for x in (top, bottom) if pd.notna(x) and str(x).strip() and str(x).strip().lower() != 'nan']\n        flat_cols.append('_'.join(parts))\n    df.columns = flat_cols\n\n    value_cols = [c for c in df.columns if c.endswith('_Tag') or c.endswith('_Enterococcus')]\n    id_cols = [c for c in df.columns if c not in value_cols]\n\n    melted = df.melt(id_vars=id_cols, value_vars=value_cols, var_name='Variable', value_name='Value')\n    melted[['Location', 'Measure']] = melted['Variable'].str.rsplit('_', n=1, expand=True)\n\n    tidy = melted.pivot(index=id_cols + ['Location'], columns='Measure', values='Value').reset_index()\n    tidy.columns.name = None\n    tidy['3-Day Rain'] = pd.to_numeric(tidy['3-Day Rain'], errors='coerce')\n\n    # Convert Enterococcus values, respecting optional Tag column such as '<'\n    entero = pd.to_numeric(tidy['Enterococcus'], errors='coerce')\n    if 'Tag' in tidy.columns:\n        tag = tidy['Tag'].astype(str).str.strip()\n        entero = entero.where(tag.ne('<'), entero)\n    tidy['Enterococcus'] = entero\n    return tidy\n\n\nresults = {}\nfor name, path in files.items():\n    tidy = load_tidy(path)\n    failures = tidy[(tidy['3-Day Rain'].eq(0)) & (tidy['Enterococcus'].ge(104))]\n    results[name] = int(len(failures))\n\nprint(results)", "reason": "Rewrote the code to use the sandbox-local CSV files, correctly parse the two-row header after skipping the title row, reshape the beach/location Enterococcus columns into tidy form, and compute counts of failed swimming-standard samples where 3-Day Rain equals 0 for the requested datasheets. The script prints the result."}) [toolUseId=call_95IC4tpPj7FQlwUlLof1A1Bz]
